accessibility.text: How do we solve problems recursively?
How do we solve problems recursively?
A common programming task is searching a data structure for a specific element. If you have no information about the data in the list, then your algorithm will be some variation of:
Loop through the entire list, compare each element to your search key.
If you found key, return the index.
If you got to the end of the list, key is not there, return -1.
This algorithm is known as a sequential search, because you have to go through the entire sequence of values to look for the key.
There is no better way to do this.
